CONTRIBUTING.md
     1â†’Contributing
     3â†’
     4â†’All the contributions are welcome! Please open [an
     5â†’issue](https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv/issues/new) or send us
     6â†’a pull request.
     7â†’
     8â†’Executing the tests:
     9â†’
    10â†’    $ uv venv
    11â†’    $ uv pip install -r requirements.txt
    12â†’    $ uv pip install -e .
    13â†’    $ uv ruff check .
    14â†’    $ uv format .
    15â†’    $ uv run pytest
    16â†’
    17â†’or with [tox](https://pypi.org/project/tox/) installed:
    18â†’
    19â†’    $ tox
    20â†’
    21â†’
    22â†’Use of pre-commit is recommended:
    23â†’
    24â†’    $ uv run precommit install
    25â†’
    26â†’
    27â†’Documentation is published with [mkdocs]():
    28â†’
    29â†’```shell
    30â†’$ uv pip install -r requirements-docs.txt
    31â†’$ uv pip install -e .
    32â†’$ uv run mkdocs serve
    33â†’```
    34â†’
